{"id":1675,"date":"2017-08-05T20:17:11","date_gmt":"2017-08-06T03:17:11","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.urbanmonk.com\/?p=1675"},"modified":"2017-08-05T20:17:11","modified_gmt":"2017-08-06T03:17:11","slug":"collateral-beauty","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"http:\/\/www.urbanmonk.com\/2017\/08\/05\/collateral-beauty\/","title":{"rendered":"Collateral Beauty"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>We watched this movie the other night. Profound, positive, a real joy to experience. But be prepared! Bring Kleenex!!!!<\/p>\n<p>Billed as a modern fable, the movie stars Will Smith as a father who has lost his six-year old daughter. The loss sends him into a tail spin. He ceases functioning in his job as co-owner and creative genius of a media company. His business partner, played by Edward Norton, and a couple other partners and fellow-workers conspire to get him out of his lethargy, at least long enough to sign a deal to sell the company before it totally collapses.<\/p>\n<p>Howard (Will Smith) writes letters to &#8220;Love&#8221;, &#8220;Time&#8221;, and &#8220;Death&#8221; as part of his attempts to deal with his grief. His co-workers, and friends, hire three actors to play the parts of these concepts and confront him.<\/p>\n<p>That is the gist of the story. I will refrain from telling more; you need to see this movie!!!<\/p>\n<p>The movie stars some big-name actors. In addition to the above, Helen Mirren, Keira Knightley, Kate Winslet also star. The movie is done very well; it is a well-told tale. Check it out.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>We watched this movie the other night. Profound, positive, a real joy to experience. But be prepared! Bring Kleenex!!!! Billed as a modern fable, the movie stars Will Smith as a father who has lost his six-year old daughter. The &hellip; <a href=\"http:\/\/www.urbanmonk.com\/2017\/08\/05\/collateral-beauty\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"